THE PILOT REPORTED THAT DURING THE LANDING ROLL, THE RIGHT MAIN 
LANDING GEAR WHEEL ADAPTOR BROKE. THE FAILURE CAUSED THE PILOT TO LOSE 
DIRECTIONAL CONTROL AND THE AIRPLANE SUBSEQUENTLY OVERTURNED. 
EXAMINATION OF THE WHEEL ADAPTOR DISCLOSED EVIDENCE OF TORSIONAL 
TENSILE OVERLOAD. THERE WAS NO EVIDENCE OF FATIGUE. 
